{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 2297852, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sounalius", "body": "I must say, Xavius's model looks terrible in my opinion. It hardly resembles a satyr [i](Despite his said \"abilities\" or not)[/i]. The face looks like someone took a flat mallet and bashed it in. All around the skeleton used just looks incredibly awkward. Blizzard could do better, much better.", "date": "2016-01-13T16:44:17-06:00", "rating": -25, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Well, he woudn't keep a pretty face after being empowered by both the Legion and an Old God. He would oviously look like an abomination and that's what Blizzard designed. He's not supposed to be the average satyr at any moment, after all.", "creationdate": "2016-01-15T17:45:27-06:00", "id": 925080, "rating": 16, "commentid": 2297852, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Yoco", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 2312121, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Reignac", "body": "Xavius was the first satyr ever. He was originally a Highborne night elf and the person who first accidentally contacted Sargeras, beginning the Legion's invasion of Azeroth 10,000 years ago. After he was killed by Malfurion Sargeras tortured his spirit and then recreated him as a satyr. When Xavius kidnapped Tyrande, Malfurion would turn him into a tree and believed he died in the Sundering.\n\nXavius returned in the novel Stormrage, where it was revealed that the Old Gods had saved him and he was the leader of the Emerald Nightmare. [url=http://legion.wowhead.com/npc=96185/thura]Thura[/url], the niece of [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=113355/broxigar-the-red]Broxigar[/url], helped Malfurion slay Xavius by using Brox's axe to chop the tree down. Turns out that didn't stop him forever, because he's back again.", "date": "2016-03-05T07:41:34-06:00", "rating": 55, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "It also should be noted that he is the one who created Sharas'dal, Scepter of Tides (the restoration shaman artifact) for Queen Aszhara and that it was her favorite gift bestowed on her during her coronation.", "creationdate": "2020-10-11T21:36:33-05:00", "id": 1395822, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2312121, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "KenjiT28", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-09-15T16:46:05-05:00", 1, "Reignac"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 2340462, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Songoo", "body": "The horns on his back are just like these of C'Thraxxi (Faceless Generals)", "date": "2016-06-14T16:08:46-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mkU0ckOvKsE", "creationdate": "2016-09-22T05:19:32-05:00", "id": 983529, "rating": -18, "commentid": 2340462, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Abohassan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He actualy uses the C'thraxxi(like Vezax) skeletton and animations", "creationdate": "2016-09-27T18:11:31-05:00", "id": 987276, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2340462, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ONCHEhap", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 2411902, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ugosatania", "body": "After the heroes slay the Nightmare Lord, there is a small chiming sound. Sentimental music plays, and an image of Queen Azshara materializes in front of Xavius, looking down upon him.\n\n[i]Queen Azshara's illusion stands over the fallen Xavius.[/i]\n[i]Xavius reaches and grabs Aszhara by the collar.[/i]\nXavius: Azshara... is it over?\n[i]Azshara grips Xavius's hand.[/i]\nAzshara: At long last. No Nightmare Lord rules forever, buddy.\nXavius: I see only...shadow tentacles ... before...me...\n[i]Xavius's weird red eyes slowly close as he now lay, lifeless. The Horn of Nightmare separates with a hiss from Xavius, laying nearby.[/i]\nAzshara bowed her head, then solemnly said.\nAzshara: Without its lord, the Nightmare will become an even greater threat to this world.\n Azshara: Control must be maintained. There must always be\n[i]A chill wind blows throughout the Rift, shadows forming at the boundries to the great dark[/i]\nAzshara: A Nightmare Lord.\n[i]Azshara's ghost disappears in a flash in front of Malfurion[/i]\n[i]Malfurion looks at the dead body of Xavius, the Horn of Nightmare gleaming darkly at his head.[/i]\nMalfurion: The weight of such a burden... it must be mine for there is no other..\nCenarius: Malfurion! You hold a grim destiny in your hands, Night Elf, but it is not your own.\nMalfurion: Cenarius! Surely you...\nCenarius: Xavius's corruption sealed my fate, and the green hills of the Dream can no longer comfort me.\nCenarius: Place the Horn of Nightmare upon my hand Malfurion, forever more I shall be the Nightmare Lord.\nMalfurion: No old friend, I cannot..\nCenarius: DO IT MALFURION! You and these ninja looters have your own destinies to fulfill.This last act of service is mine.\n[i]Malfurion holds the Horn of Nightmare closer to Cenarius[/i]\nMalfurion: You will not be forgotten, Shan'do..\nCenarius: I MUST BE FORGOTTEN, MALFURION! If the Dream is to be free from the tyranny of the Nightmare, they must never know what was done here today.\n[i]Malfurion nods grimly before sliding the Horn of Nightmare slowly over Cenarius's hand as the Rift begins to shake, causing furious shadows to spew from the darkness, whispers of dark intent at their ears[/i]\n[i]Cenarius's eyes become red and the Horn releases waves of shadows[/i]\nCenarius: Tell them only that Xavius is dead and that Cenarius...Died with HIM!\n[i]Cenarius's voice morphs and begins turning into Xavius's[/i]\nCenarius: Now GO! Leave this place and NEVER return!", "date": "2016-09-23T08:16:17-05:00", "rating": 47, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "ninja looters: We Shall Return (next week) and stop this credit ninja (again). Tirion Fordring had met his final justice(?) and light(?), yours will not be far away.", "creationdate": "2016-10-06T11:28:18-05:00", "id": 992515, "rating": -2, "commentid": 2411902, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "shininggod", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-09-23T08:29:42-05:00", 1, "Ugosatania"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 2413379, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "Phlynch", "body": "Yeah, sorry, I can't take this guy seriously.\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=101403/shade-of-xavius]This version,[/url] he's intimidating, he looks intelligent and dangerous.\r\n\r\nBut this guy looks like a feral pig goat who learned to stand up. I don't care how spiky and red this guy is, I just can't be afraid of him.", "date": "2016-09-24T20:59:38-05:00", "rating": 33, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Felt like that version looked too much like the standard satyr model", "creationdate": "2016-09-25T09:09:10-05:00", "id": 985648, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2413379, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mraceofspades", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He actually vaguely looks like a C'thraxxi (remember vezax for example),his body was deformed and mutilated by the old gods,he went through 2 deaths and you find him in the most corrupted place in the whole emerald dream. After being corrupted by both the necrotic void energies of the old gods and the fel energies he looks grotesque and deformed of course. I think he is aware of his fucked up appearance and that's why he appeared as a Satyr shade in Val'sharah,to look more intimidating.", "creationdate": "2016-09-27T18:03:59-05:00", "id": 987269, "rating": 8, "commentid": 2413379, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ONCHEhap", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If Wowpedia is true, then Xavius can take on any form he desires within the nightmare. So he chose to look like a freak pig that never heard of leg day.", "creationdate": "2016-09-27T23:33:11-05:00", "id": 987441, "rating": 12, "commentid": 2413379, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "TheQuasars", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You're not supposed to be afraid of Xavius in his actual form. He throws out an image of himself as an indimiating, intelligent, and dangerous elf... but in reality he's a corrupted feral pig goat.", "creationdate": "2016-10-09T03:16:09-05:00", "id": 993875, "rating": 5, "commentid": 2413379, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Icarus509", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I don't understand the hatred behind this design, this is clearly another case of the corrupted growing more corrupted, IE, classic Ganondorf into Ganon scenario. Considering he is working for the Old Gods and one of them is directly responsible for helping Xavius spread the Nightmare, its only fitting that the more he stays in the nightmare the more his visage twists, turns and churns out this more nightmarish form. He is still the same Xavius we have come to learn, its just his body now matches the truly black, twisted heart of its owner, a hulking nightmarish monstrosity.", "creationdate": "2016-10-26T03:51:53-05:00", "id": 1001167, "rating": 5, "commentid": 2413379, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "UncleJulio", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
