{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 2439357, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kiyoine", "body": "As a feral druid, I'll get the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=206005/dream-simulacrum]Dream Simulacrum[/url] buff while - of course - in feral cat form. I can look down and see my snoozing kitty form on the floor. However, when it expires, I am awakened and thrown back into nelf. Why! Why this?\r\n\r\nMy raid group's main tank is a guardian druid, and he goes to sleep as a bear and wakes up as a bear. Is this a bug? Intended? Why do you enjoy messing with with the flow of feral combat, Blizz?", "date": "2016-11-02T23:12:03-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
