{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 2377843, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "iamnightmare", "body": "In Stormrage, Xavius was destroyed as nightmare lord by Malfurion in both Azeroth and Emerald dream at the same time. \r\n\r\nHow is it that he came back?", "date": "2016-08-31T05:32:35-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Most probably in most cliche way ever: he wasn't really destroyed, a part of him remained, and the dark forces have brought him back.", "creationdate": "2016-09-02T12:03:08-05:00", "id": 966424, "rating": 6, "commentid": 2377843, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Vagiulis", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yeah, my cat laid an egg yesterday which hatched into a flying elephant. Probably dark forces involved there too.", "creationdate": "2016-09-06T08:20:55-05:00", "id": 969788, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2377843, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "iamnightmare", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Xavius died twice before then, the first time Sargeras revived him and the second time it was the Old Gods. So clearly this third revival was one of them, most likely Sargeras since he's (allegedly) on the Legion's side this time.", "creationdate": "2016-09-15T16:44:28-05:00", "id": 978806, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2377843, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Reignac", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 2403008, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Reignac", "body": "Xavius was the first satyr ever. He was originally a Highborne night elf and the person who first accidentally contacted Sargeras, beginning the Legion's invasion of Azeroth 10,000 years ago. After he was killed by Malfurion Sargeras tortured his spirit and then recreated him as a satyr. When Xavius kidnapped Tyrande, Malfurion would turn him into a tree and believed he died in the Sundering.\n\nXavius returned in the novel Stormrage, where it was revealed that the Old Gods had saved him and he was the leader of the Emerald Nightmare. [url=http://legion.wowhead.com/npc=96185/thura]Thura[/url], the niece of [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=113355/broxigar-the-red]Broxigar[/url], helped Malfurion slay Xavius by using Brox's axe to chop the tree down. Turns out that didn't stop him forever, because he's back again.", "date": "2016-09-15T16:43:35-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-09-15T16:45:37-05:00", 2, "Reignac"]}
